          <h5 class="card-title">AWS Site to Site VPN connection </h5>
          <p class="card-text lead"> If we want to connect our on-premises data center to an AWS VPN then we may use Site-to-Site VPN connectivity. 
            <br> It requires two main things:
            <ul>
                <li class="lead">Virtual Private Gateway on AWS side</li>
                <li class="lead">Customer gateway on the client side</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">Virtual Private Gateway (VGW)</h5>
              <p class="card-text lead">It is a VPN concentrator and helps establish a VPN connection from client to AWS network.
              </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">Customer Gateway (CGW)</h5>
